cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.LO, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses choreographic approaches to message-passing applications, which can be regarded as an instance of model-driven development principles. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper proposes a new local model, group interface automata, to represent the local view of choreographies. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with interactions among distributed participants coordinating among themselves with message-passing. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper discusses the verification of well-formed conditions on global views, which can be seen as a logical problem. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions the algorithmic obtainment of the communication pattern of each participant.
